CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, January 27, 1962, page 15, reads: "Blankets For Refugees - When the Pittsburgh Council of Churchwomen made an emergency call for new and used blankets, to be sent to refugees in stricken areas, among the hundreds who headed the call were these AME Zionites. Left to right: Mrs. A. Harrington, A. Miller, C. Haynes, E. Betts, official board representative; I. Tolivar, M. Foggie, E. Hawkins, I. Glenn and M. Franklin. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Group portrait of nine Pittsburgh Council of Churchwomen members, from left: Mrs. A. Harrington, A. Miller, C. Haynes, E. Betts, I. Tolivar, Madeline Foggie, E. Hawkins, I. Glenn and M. Franklin, holding light colored blanket, in church with arched stained glass window and checkered floor, another version
